txt.en: '...and I said to Iris, \qIf you've never been to Buckland, how do you know they're that queer at all? They could be as normal as you or me.\q'
'You know, I never thought about it like that. So, have you ever been to Buckland?'
'What? Me go to Buckland? Are you mad?'
'W-w-waaah.'
'Oh, hello! I'll just stop for a nibble....'
'Always room for a chew with your brew, my dad always says.'
'Did that fellow just eat my dinner?'
'That there's my family recipe. Lots of folk have been borrowing copies. But why did you have to go wake me up?'
'Oh, look -- food! I'm rather hungry....'
'Your friend still not here?'
'So rude... zzz....'
'I'll show them who's... yellow! Tomorrow, I'm going straight... to the office of the Watch and sign up! I'm going... to be a Bounder!'
'I'm sleepy.'
'Oh! It's my burrow! Excellent, I can go sleep in bed.'
'No, not yet....'
Inn League Member
'...where did my home go? It was just here.'
'I'm sure he'll be along shortly.'
'Cheers to you... friend!'
'Nooo! N-nooo! Poor beer... you were too young to die!'
'My head feels funny. Where am I?'
'You think you're tough? I bet I could lift... six sacks of grain... all at the same time!'
'You look like a logical fellow....'
'Mmm, I'm awfully sleepy.'
'Perhaps you can give me some advice.'
'Hey! You're a barrel! Nice try, barrel... I almost told you all my secrets.'
'Oh, Boro, you're so witty!'
'Whoops!'
'Ha! You can't handle your ale! How embarassing for you.'
'Those fool Bolgers don't know what they have! I mark up them hogs I buy from them by three, and my customers thank me for my trade.'
'Uh huh....'
'Fish? The only thing that ought eat fish is other fish! Sheeps, cows, pigs... that's what proper hobbits ought... eat!'
'There's my house! I found it!'
'You want to talk about cooking? I've got two words for you: coneys... that's the secret to a... great meal!'
'Uh huh....'
